cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on quantifying the differential privacy guarantees of gossip protocols. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the tradeoff between spreading time and differential privacy. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper considers wireless networks and unreliable links. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as gossip protocols are commonly used in social networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of noise as a privacy protection tool.
